Context("Numeric");
#given
$c = random(50,200,5); #mA
$t = random(1,2,.01); #ms


#image scale
$imgScale =0.4;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*875;
$height = $imgScale*720;

#computation
$tau = 8*$c/1000;
$vDE = -6*exp((-$t/($tau)));

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.01);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "UBC-CIR-17-022.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

In the following network, calculate the voltage [`V_{DE}`] [`[$t]`] seconds after the switch is opened. Take the capacitance to be [`C=[$c]`] [`\mu F`].

[`V_{DE}=`] [_____]{"$vDE"} [`V`]  

